✅ Do’s
Think before posting – Make sure your content reflects positively on you.
Protect your privacy – Use strong passwords and adjust privacy settings.
Verify information – Share only accurate and reliable content.
Be respectful – Communicate politely, even in disagreements.
Manage your time – Set limits so social media doesn’t affect studies or sleep.
❌ Don’ts
Don’t overshare personal details – Avoid posting sensitive information (address, phone number, etc.).
Don’t engage in online fights – Arguments can harm your reputation.
Don’t post inappropriate content – It can impact future academic or job opportunities.
Don’t believe everything you see – Be cautious of fake news and misinformation.
Don’t ignore digital footprint – Remember, what you post online can stay forever.
